meanings.sent1: She outdelivered her competitors by delivering the packages faster.
meanings.sent2: The courier service outdelivered all expectations by delivering the goods ahead of schedule.
meanings.sent3: The race was won by the runner who outdelivered everyone else in speed and efficiency.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication to her job outdelivered any previous employee's performance.
meanings.sent5: The superhero outdelivered all villains by delivering justice swiftly and effectively.

meanings.definition: To exceed in the act of delivering
meanings.sent1: The company outdelivered its competitors by delivering top-notch customer service.
meanings.sent2: The online retailer outdelivered its promise of same-day delivery by actually delivering within hours.
meanings.sent3: The magician outdelivered the audience's expectations by delivering a mind-blowing performance.
meanings.sent4: The chef outdelivered himself by delivering a culinary masterpiece that amazed everyone.
meanings.sent5: The team outdelivered all others by delivering a flawless presentation that impressed the judges.
